docs.lead_paragraph: It was nearly midnight on Wednesday when Los Angeles Dodgers first baseman Adrian Gonzalez sent a pitch from Pedro Feliciano into left field for a double, producing a come-from-behind 5-4 victory over the New York Mets in what has become season of heroics for the Major League Baseball team.

headline.main: Los Angeles Dodgers Streak Into History Books
